      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix and bake",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 180°C (160°C fan). Grease two 20 cm round tins and line the bases. Beat {{unsalted-butter}} and {{caster-sugar}} until pale and fluffy, about 4 minutes. Beat in the {{eggs}} one at a time, then stir in the {{coffee-instant}} solution. Fold in {{self-raising-flour}} and {{baking-powder}}, then fold through the {{walnuts}}. Divide between the tins and bake for 20 to 22 minutes until a skewer comes out clean. Cool in tins for 5 minutes, then turn onto a rack.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make buttercream and assemble",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Beat the buttercream {{unsalted-butter}}, {{icing-sugar}}, and {{coffee-instant}} solution until smooth and light. Spread half on the bottom layer, then sandwich with the second sponge. Spread the remaining buttercream over the top. Press walnut halves around the edge to decorate.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
